Project made with python to collect, clean, and train a model for object detection on RGBD images.
The model will be used to detect rocks and creators in a depth image.
The first step was to convert a video of the depth and RGB image into frames, which was done using an online resource.
Second, RANSAC was used to create a ground plane that shows any obstacles that might be above or below the ground.
Third, DBSCAN and DGSCAN were used to make labels and bounding boxes for any object.
Finally, the model was trained using YOLOv8



# RANSAC
python3 ransac_pipeline.py

# labels and bounding boxes
python3 mask_to_yolo.py \
    --image_dir data/images \
    --mask_dir  data/masks \
    --label_dir data/labels \
    --visualize

# Prep and Splitting data 
python3 prepare_dataset.py \
    --image_dir data/images \
    --label_dir data/labels \
    --output_dir dataset

# Compress images for Colab
zip -r colab_zip_images.zip data/images data/masks mask_to_yolo.py prepare_dataset.py train_yolo.py

# Train
python3 train_yolo.py \
    --data dataset/dataset.yaml \
    --model yolov8n.pt \
    --epochs 100 \
    --batch 16 \
    --device cpu



#I am using a venv to keep track of python3 and yolo dependensies
source ~/rover_venv/bin/activate


